You know what sucks? Be disappointed by a place you like. Came in here again, like plenty of times before, to get Waffle fries to go (which are really outstanding). I ordered right away and sat down at the bar waiting. I saw how after a few minutes my order was out and ready to go. It was brought to the bar, and left for the bartender to see it and give it to me. There were two bartenders this night, they were NOT busy, and neither of them handed me the food. I saw how the girl who took my order just had a conversation with her friend at the bar, and ate what seemed like chicken fingers, while my food was just sitting there, bye bye crispy waffle fries. After like 5 minutes they realize I was staring and decided I could have the food I paid for. I now wish I hadn’t left a 30% tip, because apparently the fact that I was only there to get food to go was unimportant to ‘Bianca’, which is the name of the bartender who “took care” of me, according to the receipt. This happened on Wednesday August 1st of 2018, at 9:20pm, and it’ll be the last time I’ll come to this place. Not worth the trip from Brooklyn if I’m not going to be given the proper service.

At The Wallace is probably my favorite bar in the neighborhood - and there is no short list from which to choose. Comfortable and ample seating, not crazy (unless it's a thurs-sun night) and good drink prices. I don't think they have a happy hour really, but the prices are about what you'd expect to pay at any happy hour - only all the time! 4-5$ drafts and 6-8$ cocktails seem to be the norm here, no matter the time of day. There are plenty of fun catchy things here to occupy yourself with in-between gulps; such as huge-sized Jenga, that little plastic boxing game where you and someone would mad-mash two buttons until someone's head eventually pops off, cards and way more.  No matter the day, you can normally find me At The Wallace ;) (Was that too corny?)
